text:
It looks like that healing set is meant for Kokomi but I feel like it's going to be more suitable to make Barbara deal fairly decent damage. If I'm understanding it correctly, you would pop her skill and fire off a few normal attacks to heal the party and create a Sea-Dyed Foam. Use her Burst to charge the foam to it's maximum (30k) and then have someone like Venti or Kazuha group enemies onto it, allowing it to explode on the group for 27k (90% of 30k) AoE damage. Not fantastic, but better than a few normal and charged attacks.

The wording is a bit confusing on what type of damage is dealt but I assume it's based on the type of healing perhaps? In my example, it would be Hydro, but if this set were equipped to, let's say Bennett, it would be Pyro, And charging the Sea-Dyed Foam with both would cause a vape reaction but not the vape damage bonus. 

I also believe that defense set might be good for a damage Noelle build, but we'll see.

Here‚Äôs my theory on this I don‚Äôt think Cryo Albedo is the real Albedo hence the word Shadows in ‚ÄúShadows Amidst Snowstorms‚Äù. Since Albedo‚Äôs research revolves around the creation of life it isn‚Äôt to far fetched that someone stole his research to create another version of him. The avalanche is created by Cryo Albedo which Albedo got caught in, resulting in him going missing. Eula and the others came across Cryo Albedo thinking it‚Äôs Albedo unknown to them that he‚Äôs still missing.

The reason I think Cryo Albedo can wield Cryo because he‚Äôs a artificial human therefore he doesn‚Äôt need a vision to manipulate elements. Albedo has hinted that Traveler is like him, made of chalk; an artificial life form made of a superior substance. If Albedo is similar to Traveler- who can wield multiple elements without a vision- then theoretically it should be possible for Albedo to do the same, hence Cryo Albedo.

text:
For the record: I am not a Bible scholar, and have no formal training in any way. In fact, I am a High School dropout and have never taken a college course or any theology classes. I‚Äôve never read a ‚ÄòCommentary‚Äô on any Scripture, I can‚Äôt read Hebrew, Greek or any language other than English.

I say all that to say this: If you glean anything from what I'm about to say you need to know it is from the Living God. Not me. The confidence I have in His word comes from Him. The faith that I have in His ability to transform and redeem lives comes from Him and from personal experience. The knowledge I have of the Living God (the God of the Bible) comes from knowing Him and His inspired word, and my understanding of it comes from the indwelling of His Holy Spirit. I do not proclaim to know all that there is to know about the Lord, but what I do know I am grateful to have the opportunity to share with you. The Lord gave me LIFE when I was living in the deepest darkness‚Ä¶with no hope‚Ä¶or a future‚Ä¶ and I am here because I was not alone in that darkness and I want YOU to know the God that saves. [If you don‚Äôt already] . And If you do, then I pray you will join me in my quest to bring God‚Äôs glorious light into the darkness that is consuming our world. Not for my sake‚Ä¶but for the sake of those who are still lost. Join me in crying, ‚ÄúCome to the cross of Jesus! He is MIGHTY TO SAVE!‚Äù

You need to know that there is irrefutable evidence that God‚Äôs word was written by One who knows the end from the beginning, so don‚Äôt believe the lie that all believers in Him have a ‚Äòblind‚Äô faith that is based on ‚Äòfeelings‚Äô, and nothing more. Many of us came to Christ with blind faith [with little to no knowledge of God], but if we‚Äôre growing in our relationship with Him and the knowledge of His word we will grow into a mature Christian that cannot be swayed by false teachers, mockers, or staunch unbelievers, for how can we deny one we KNOW? And how can we not defend the One who has redeemed us, transformed us, and given us eternal life?

I am not still following Christ with blind faith‚Ä¶but am, rather, walking towards heaven with my eyes wide open‚Ä¶confident in the God I serve‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶and I just want to make my Heavenly Father proud.

.

text:
The word of God says that we have all sinned. All of us. And sins penalty is death. The good news of the Bible is that God loves us so much He didn‚Äôt want us to have to pay the penalty for our sins so He paid the penalty for us! He literally died for us‚Ä¶so we wouldn‚Äôt have to! And because he‚Äôs God he rose from the dead to prove that He was who He told everyone He was‚Ä¶and, [His word tells us] to prove that He was successful in doing what He came to do. To pay the penalty of our sin in full.

So does that mean that everyone gets to go to heaven now? No. Everyone could‚Ä¶.but everyone won‚Äôt. Because not everyone is grateful that Jesus died for them. And some people don‚Äôt even feel guilty for their sin. They like sinning. And for that reason they will reject Jesus. Some people just don‚Äôt believe in Jesus. Some are so crazy they don‚Äôt even believe He ever even existed, even though there‚Äôs irrefutable evidence and proof that He did. And others think they‚Äôre pretty good people‚Ä¶and think they can earn their way to heaven because of that goodness. The problem is they‚Äôre comparing themselves to other people. People who are worse than them of course. And we don‚Äôt get to go to heaven because we‚Äôre ‚Äúbetter than our neighbors.‚Äù No sin can enter heaven. None. Period. And bottom line is only those who have repented of their sins‚Ä¶asked Jesus to forgive them for their sins‚Ä¶believed that He died for their sins‚Ä¶and asked Him to save them‚Ä¶will go to heaven. God made heaven. It belongs to Him. And He is the One who gets to decide who can go there, and who can‚Äôt. He has made a way for all of us to be able to go to heaven‚Ä¶but many people are so arrogant they think they can do it ‚Äúthere way‚Äù and still get there. :( They‚Äôre wrong.

To repent means to not only admit you have sinned‚Ä¶but to be truly sorry in your heart for sinning as well. [Not sorry because you got caught‚Ä¶but sorry that you ever did it‚Ä¶there‚Äôs a big difference.] Repentance is the key ingredient to salvation that many people overlook. They think they can just pray a prayer‚Ä¶like it‚Äôs magic or something‚Ä¶and be saved. But that is not the case. Repentance is a requirement because God only forgives those who are sincerely sorry for what they have done. Just saying ‚ÄúI‚Äôm sorry‚Äù is not good enough‚Ä¶it‚Äôs all about what‚Äôs in our hearts.

Think of it this way. Do you have any siblings? Or cousins? Or someone in your life that‚Äôs done something to hurt you‚Ä¶that then had your mom or dad or someone tell them to apologize to you for what they did? And then they looked at you and said, ‚ÄúSorry,‚Äù in such a way that it was obvious they were not sorry and were only saying ‚Äúsorry‚Äù because someone in authority over them was making them do it? That is the opposite of ‚Äúrepentance.‚Äù It‚Äôs only words. It meant nothing because they didn‚Äôt mean it and they wouldn‚Äôt have even said it if they hadn‚Äôt been made to. Now, if you can tell the difference between when someone is truly sorry, and when they‚Äôre just saying ‚Äúwords‚Äù how much more can God‚Ä¶who knows everything! Our every thought! Our every deed! If we‚Äôre not truly sorry‚Ä¶we will not be forgiven. But, if we are truly sorry‚Ä¶and we ask Him to forgive us‚Ä¶He will do it! Immediately. And when we do that‚Ä¶and we believe that He paid the penalty for that sin‚Ä¶and all of our sin‚Ä¶and ask Him to save us‚Ä¶He will do it. Immediately. It‚Äôs all about what‚Äôs in our heart. Being sincere.

And, if you don‚Äôt know Jesus yet, then today you can ask Him to forgive you for your sins‚Ä¶[but only if you mean it]‚Ä¶and you can repent of them‚Ä¶tell Him you don‚Äôt want to keep sinning and you need His help to change‚Ä¶and put your faith in what Jesus did for you on the cross‚Ä¶paying your sin debt in full. The choice is yours, the Lord has given you a free will‚Ä¶and He loves you so very much. But He will never force you to love Him in return.

We are, right now, very late in the Biblical ‚Äúend days‚Äù‚Ä¶and the return of Christ for his church prior to the start of the tribulation that will follow is ‚Äúat the door,‚Äù so I hope you‚Äôll consider what God‚Äôs word has to say about the days we‚Äôre living in and those that are soon coming, because although people can still place their faith in Christ after the rapture they will then lose their lives as a result of their newfound faith as the Antichrist will have no tolerance for those who choose Christ over him. Only 1/3 of those who enter the tribulation will still be alive at the end of those 7 years. The horror of it is, quite simply, incomprehensible. :( If you don‚Äôt yet know Christ‚Ä¶please‚Ä¶please don‚Äôt wait. Today is the day of salvation. Jesus desires for all to be saved‚Ä¶for none to perish, and we know from His word that is why He has tarried in these end days before coming! But‚Ä¶He will come‚Ä¶soon‚Ä¶because He is the God of His word‚Ä¶and if He said it‚Ä¶He must bring it to pass.

If you‚Äôre interested in knowing what‚Äôs going on I can tell you with 100% certainty what is happening in our world. Why it‚Äôs happening. And what‚Äôs coming next.

You see, 2000 years ago [and more] we were told by Daniel, Ezekiel, Isaiah, Matthew, Luke, John, Paul, and Peter among others [inspired by God], what would happen in ‚Äúour‚Äù generation! The ‚Äúend day‚Äù generation‚Ä¶

Why our generation? Because‚Ä¶for reasons only God knows‚Ä¶He himself predetermined that He would fulfill His ‚Äúend day‚Äù prophecies during our lifetime. And so, as He inspired those who loved and served Him to write His word He gave us precise signs and ‚Äúprophecies‚Äù that would be fulfilled in our generation, so that, we would ‚Äúknow that He is God.‚Äù In fact, the word of God prophesied a great many details about the days we‚Äôre living in. More than most even realize!

One of the most important keys to interpreting Bible prophecy is to remember that it revolves around God‚Ä¶Israel‚Ä¶and Israel‚Äôs Messiah‚Ä¶Jesus Christ. I see many making the mistake of trying to ‚Äúinterpret the prophecies‚Äù by the ‚Äúsigns‚Äù, rather than ‚Äúinterpreting the signs‚Äù by the ‚Äúprophecies‚Äù. I didn‚Äôt really think about that until I responded to a comment I received from a man who believes we are already in the ‚Äútribulation‚Äù prophesied in Revelation 6‚Äì18. He is making that exact mistake which is terribly heartbreaking. He‚Äôs seeing ‚Äúsigns‚Äù and then is looking for ‚Äúprophecies‚Äù to match them. In doing so he is misinterpreting Bible prophecy. And, as a result, [in his own words], he‚Äôs living in daily torment as he sincerely believes many have been deceived and have unwittingly received the ‚Äúmark of the beast‚Äù, [which seals the eternal fate‚Äîto hell‚Äî of those who receive it] from Revelation 13 [which has not yet been implemented]. I don‚Äôt know if he is telling individuals that they now have no chance of being saved, [referring to those in some countries, who are already using a monetary system that involves them being ‚Äúscanned‚Äù in some way, with a chip in their body, but the implications are horrific if he is!] Telling people that they are now condemned to hell, when in fact they are NOT‚Ä¶ and telling them they have received a ‚Äúmark‚Äù that isn‚Äôt even yet the ‚Äúmark‚Äù of Revelation 13 is‚Ä¶well‚Ä¶just unimaginable. :('

text:
When we misinterpret one Scripture it usually snowballs into others as well, and the result can be devastating in our lives‚Ä¶and the lives of those we influence! :( Although the signs of the times are all around us, the ‚Äúcurrent‚Äù signs are all ‚Äúpre-tribulation‚Äù signs pointing to a specific timeframe that will be unmistakable when it begins. Signs that are screaming‚Ä¶‚ÄùLook up! Your redemption is near!‚Äù [For those who know Christ.] And, ‚ÄúRepent, Jesus is coming!‚Äù [For those who don‚Äôt know Christ yet.] :(

The book of Revelation is casting a long dark shadow over our world right now, but the prophecies of that book have not yet started. When they do people will KNOW it. The tribulation has a starting point that many don‚Äôt realize. And it‚Äôs not found in the book of Revelation. Yes, there are 4 ‚Äúhorsemen‚Äù who are ‚Äúsent out‚Äù in Revelation 6‚Ä¶early in the ‚Äútribulation‚Äù, but, as I mentioned many are already misinterpreting current events as matching up with those ‚Äúapocalyptic‚Äù prophecies, and they have NOT yet started their fulfillment, because the ‚Äútrigger‚Äù event for the beginning of the tribulation, or ‚Äú70th week of Daniel‚Äù has not yet occurred.

What we must do is look at the ‚Äúprophecies‚Äù, and then wait and watch for them to be fulfilled. The ‚Äútribulation‚Äù, as it is called by most who know anything about Bible prophecy is a very specific ‚Äútimeframe‚Äù. That timeframe is not revealed fully in Revelation. We know it ‚Äúends‚Äù with the Second Coming of Christ prophesied in Revelation 19, but Revelation doesn‚Äôt give us a telling, specific, clearly identifiable ‚Äúevent‚Äù that ‚Äústarts‚Äù the ‚Äútribulation.‚Äù To find that ‚Äútrigger‚Äù we have to go backward in God‚Äôs word‚Ä¶to the Old Testament‚Ä¶and the book of Daniel. And there we find the ‚Äúreason‚Äù for the judgments/prophecies in Revelation‚Ä¶and the ‚Äútrigger‚Äù that starts them. Again, it‚Äôs all about Israel and God and Messiah. And with the Daniel prophecy added to the Revelation 19 prophecy we‚Äôre given ‚Äúbookend prophecies‚Äù that contain‚Ä¶within them‚Ä¶all the prophecies from Revelation 6‚Äì19 and more. Not knowing that ‚Äúleft end‚Äù bookend causes a lot of confusion‚Ä¶and a lot of misinterpretation of Scripture. :( First‚Ä¶the ‚Äúreason‚Äù for the soon coming 7 years of judgment. Found in Daniel 9:24.

Daniel 9:24: ‚ÄúSeventy ‚Äòsevens‚Äô are decreed for your people and your holy city to finish transgression, to put an end to sin, to atone for wickedness, to bring in everlasting righteousness, to seal up vision and prophecy and to anoint the most holy.‚Äù

That verse gives us the ‚Äúreason‚Äù for the judgments prophesied in the book of Revelation. The ‚ÄúSeventy ‚Äòsevens‚Äô‚Äù is 70 sets of 7 year periods for a total of 490 years. We know from verses 25 and 26 that ‚Äúsixty-two ‚Äòsevens‚Äô and ‚Äúseven ‚Äòsevens‚Äô‚Äù have already been fulfilled for a total of ‚Äúsixty-nine ‚Äòsevens‚Äô‚Äù, or 69 sets of ‚Äú7 year periods‚Äù for a total of 483 years of the 490 fulfilled. The study of that, and prophetic fulfillment of those timeframes is pretty involved, and is far more than anyone could post on here, but if you want to do a deeper study on it I would recommend the book, ‚ÄúThe Book of Daniel‚Äù by Clarence Larkin. It‚Äôs a little over my head, as I‚Äôm not the ‚Äúscholarly‚Äù type, but it‚Äôs thorough for sure!

The break down of Daniel 9:25‚Äì26, among other things, actually gives us the timing of the first coming of Christ, up to His violent death [the crucifixion] and the destruction of the Jewish temple in 70 A.D. around 40 years later . The prophetic word is a phenomenal gift the Lord has given us, as He reveals to His children what He is going to do‚Ä¶before He does it‚Ä¶so we can be fully prepared‚Ä¶and prepare others.

This prophecy was given over 500 years before the birth of Christ. The parenthesis will actually give the ‚Äúdates‚Äù that each part of the verse is referring to. By calculating this ‚Äúprophecy‚Äù the religious leaders during the days of Jesus could have been 100% certain Christ was the Messiah, or ‚ÄúAnointed One‚Äù Scripture had told them of. But, as Jesus told them in Matthew 16:2: ‚ÄúWhen evening comes, you say, ‚ÄòIt will be fair weather, for the sky is red,‚Äô and in the morning, ‚ÄòToday it will be stormy, for the sky is red and overcast.‚Äô You know how to interpret the appearance of the sky, but you cannot interpret the signs of the times.‚Äù What ‚Äúsigns‚Äù were they missing? Well, nearly 200 Messianic verses from the OT that told them exactly what to watch for. One of which, as I mentioned, actually gave them the date for the fulfillment of Zechariah 9:9: Rejoice greatly, O Daughter of Zion! Shout, Daughter of Jerusalem! See, your King comes to you, righteous and having salvation, gentle and riding on a donkey, on a colt, the foal of a donkey.

Daniel 9:25- ‚ÄúKnow and understand this: From the issuing of the decree to restore and rebuild Jerusalem [we find this in Nehemiah Ch. 2‚Ä¶March 5, 444 B.C.] until the Anointed One, [Messiah] the ruler, comes, there will be seven ‚Äòsevens,‚Äô and sixty-two ‚Äòsevens.‚Äô [It was 7X7 yrs (or 49 yrs.) for the city to be rebuilt and then another 62X7 yrs. (or 434 yrs, keeping in mind the Jewish calendar is 360 day years) til Messiah would come.) So, from March 5, 444 B.C. we‚Äôre told 483 years will pass before Messiah comes. What date does that take us to? Adding 173,880 days to March 5,444 B.C. takes us to March 30 A.D. 33. The exact day Christ rode into Jerusalem on the donkey as the prophecy in Zechariah foretold. A few days prior to His crucifixion. Now you may not find that to be phenomenal. But, I do! And moving on to Daniel 9:26 we see: After the sixty-two ‚Äòsevens‚Äô, the Anointed One will be cut-off [which according to Strong‚Äôs concordance refers to a ‚Äúviolent death‚Äù] and will have nothing. Violent death? Yep‚Ä¶that pretty much covers it. :( The people of the ruler who will come will destroy the city and the sanctuary. [This is referencing the destruction of the city and temple in 70 AD by the Romans some 37 yrs. later.] So, at the end of this portion of Scripture, 69 of the 70 weeks are fulfilled.

All we have left then is the final week. The ‚Äú70th of the ‚Äô70 weeks‚Äô‚Äù. 69 were fulfilled prior to the death and resurrection of Christ. One is left. The final 7 years of God‚Äôs 490 years of ‚Äúdecreed‚Äù prophecies/judgments for Israel as recorded in Daniel 9:24. So, again, when Christ was crucified, [cut off‚Äîin v.26a] the first 69 ‚Äò7 yr periods‚Äô decreed were completed. Remember this prophecy is specifically for the Jewish people. No one else. Not the church. Not the world. The Jewish people only. Daniel is told these 490 years are decreed for ‚Äúhis people.‚Äù

So, at the completion of the ‚Äò69th 7-yr period‚Äô Israel had rejected her Messiah‚Ä¶and the Lord‚Äôs ‚Äúfocus‚Äù on the Jews turned to the ‚Äúchurch.‚Äù The Biblical ‚Äúchurch age‚Äù began‚Ä¶and those who repented of their sins and placed their faith in Israel‚Äôs Messiah [Jew and Gentile alike‚Ä¶have been saved, as God has not ‚Äúrejected‚Äù his people, but they have only been ‚Äúblinded‚Äù for a time because of the hardness of their hearts and their rejection of Jesus].

[Please note: I am NOT saying that God has ‚Äúrejected‚Äù Israel as is purported in some heretical teachings. God‚Äôs covenant with Israel, through Abraham, is an ‚Äúeverlasting‚Äù covenant. Period. They are and always have been His chosen people‚Ä¶since the book of Genesis, and His focus will turn fully towards them once again in the very near future. It would be good for those who think God rejected His people after they rejected Christ as Messiah, to remember that even now, we are in the prophetic ‚Äúend days‚Äù because of fulfilled prophecies that involve Israel. Specifically their resurrection as a nation, foretold in Ezekiel 36 and 37 and more, which started the ‚Äúend day‚Äù generational clock ticking.]

Because the 490 year ‚Äúdecreed‚Äù timeclock stopped 3 days prior to the crucifixion of Messiah‚Ä¶with 7 years remaining to be fulfilled‚Ä¶those last 7 years have been waiting‚Ä¶and waiting‚Ä¶for their fulfillment as well. And now, nearly 2,000 yrs. later, the ‚Äú70th week of Daniel‚Äù is ‚Äúat the door.‚Äù We find a short description of that final week in Daniel 9:27: He [the Antichrist] will confirm a covenant with many for one ‚Äòseven.‚Äô In the middle of the ‚Äòseven‚Äô he will put an end to sacrifice and offering. And on a wing of the temple he will set up an abomination that causes desolation, until the end that is decreed is poured out on him.‚Äù

This verse tells us what ‚Äústarts‚Äù the final ‚Äúdecreed‚Äù 7-year period from the prophecy in Daniel 24. So, while most know the ‚Äúright bookend‚Äù prophecy for the tribulation, the Second Coming of Christ from Revelation 19, we find here that ‚Äúleft bookend‚Äù prophecy I mentioned earlier that triggers the start of the tribulation. A 7-yr ‚Äúcovenant‚Äù that the Antichrist confirms with many. The ‚Äúconfirms‚Äù verbiage here speaks of his ‚Äústrengthening‚Äù or ‚Äúimproving on‚Äù a covenant that is already in place. Perhaps the
Abraham Accords? I don‚Äôt know, but I believe this ‚Äòcovenant‚Äô will fall at the end of the soon coming Ezekiel 38/39 war when Russia, Iran, Turkey, Libya and Sudan come against Israel. We do know this: Israel‚Äôs ability to rebuild their temple will be a part of this long-awaited prophetic covenant
author: ResidentArtist0

text:
Jesus said in John 5:43- ‚ÄúI have come in my Father‚Äôs name, and you do not accept me; but if someone else comes in his own name, you will accept him.‚Äù

In short, this ‚Äúsomeone‚Äù that Jesus warned us of is the ‚Äúhe‚Äù that will ‚Äúconfirm the 7-yr covenant‚Äù from Daniel 9:27. And as the decreed final 7-yr period starts with the swipe of a pen, and the signing of a covenant between Israel and ‚Äúmany‚Äù we find the Jewish people at the ‚Äúcenter‚Äù of prophecy once again. And the final 7-yrs from Daniel 9:24 begins. Having rejected their Messiah 2,000 yrs earlier, we will find them ‚Äúreceiving‚Äù one who comes in his own name [on his own behalf rather than on God‚Äôs behalf]. The Biblical ‚ÄúAntichrist, Lawless One or Beast‚Äù as he is referred to throughout Scripture.

This great deceiver [a man indwelt and empowered by Satan himself], will convince the Jewish people he is their long-awaited Messiah‚Ä¶and for the first 3.5 years of his ‚Äúcovenant‚Äù, even as prophetic judgments from Revelation are beginning to fall upon the earth, they‚Äôll think he‚Äôs the greatest thing that ever happened to them as he makes it possible for them to rebuild their temple and reimplement their Old Testament sacrificial system. They have been waiting for this moment‚Ä¶and they are ready. All that they need‚Ä¶they have. Everything but the piece of land the temple will be rebuilt on. The Antichrist will provide this with the covenant. When the pen of the Antichrist hits that paper these things happen.

1. The identity of the Antichrist is revealed. He has pen in hand.

2. The tribulation or 70th week of Daniel begins. [They are one and the same 7-yr period.]

3. The identity of the rider of the white horse in Revelation 6 is now known, as the Antichrist rides out as a conqueror bent on conquest, as the first seal judgment is opened.

4. Those who are paying attention, and who have some Biblical knowledge at that time can count 2,520 days forward and pinpoint the exact day of the Second Coming of Christ for the battle of Armageddon.

5. They can also count forward 1,260 days and know the exact day the Antichrist will waltz into the newly rebuilt temple and proclaim to be God. Those who are aware of this prophetic event‚Ä¶that are Jewish‚Ä¶can get a head start on ‚Äúfleeing into the mountains‚Äù, as they are instructed to do in Matthew 24:15‚Äì16.

So, now, with the signing of the 7-yr ‚Äúcovenant,‚Äù putting the Jews at the forefront of prophecy again‚Ä¶and their final 7 years of decreed prophecies/judgments beginning their fulfillment the world will find itself in the pages of the book of Revelation. Most refer to this ‚Äú70th week of Daniel‚Äù as the ‚Äútribulation‚Äù. And if you‚Äôve ever read the book of Revelation then you know why. Of those who enter that final 7 years of Daniel‚Äôs decreed 490 years, only 1/3 will still be alive at the end of it. During the first 3.5 yrs. alone 1/4 of the earth‚Äôs population will die from war, famine, wild beasts, and pestilence. It‚Äôs going to get worse. Much, much worse.

But, praise God, there will be those who will escape this coming time of judgment. They will be removed from the earth prior to the start of that coming Ezekiel war and the covenant that ends it. We‚Äôre running out of time‚Ä¶and God‚Äôs prophecies [nearly 1/3 of His inspired word] will all be fulfilled. Many within, I believe, the next 7 to 8 years as we are currently 72 yrs. into the prophetic ‚Äúend days.‚Äù I pray you‚Äôll consider what God‚Äôs word has to say about what we are going through now‚Ä¶and what is just around the corner. There is much, much more to it than just this, but the study of ‚Äúend day‚Äù prophecies involves most of Scripture‚Ä¶and it is impossible to share it all here.

With the recent Israel/Gaza war‚Ä¶and now the drastic change in Israel‚Äôs governance just around the corner I believe it is growing more and more clear that the Ezekiel 38 war is imminent. I say that because I want to simply remind you of this: the rapture precedes that war. Jesus is coming folks‚Ä¶whether we‚Äôre ready or not! Are you ready? I pray that you are‚Ä¶

text:
Basically, we all know Albedo is from Khaenri'ah, or he's master/creator was from there by the multiple clues given (technology advanced enough to make a human out of chalk, the star on his collarbone, etc.), I'm not sure about Durin's backstory, but through Albedo's interactions with the Festering Desire, I can only assume he and Durin were somehow connected. 
Now, why would his master need to make a homunculus? It could be an assistant to help with their research, hence why Albedo has a vast knowledge on Alchemy, or it could just be an experiment? Khaenri'ah has no archon, that's what we know. And through several clues, we know Khaenri'ah is yet to be located, but it is safe to say it may be somewhere in Mondstadt's reigon/side of the map, which would be why Mond has its fair share of people from that place (Kaeya, Albedo, Dainslief)

For a nation with no God or Archon, maybe that would be what they wanted? Kaeya was a spy I suppose, probably Immortal or was reborn to be young and live with Diluc, and the "Pirate Grandfather" he speaks of could have just been himself when he was a prince in Khaenri'ah with his wealth? I can guess he died before the destruction of Khaenri'ah, which was why he truly has no goal now to complete his mission as a spy, and chose the true family he made in Mond over the father who let his own son be sent off to an enemy nation with the goal to learn more about their archon, Venti. 
We already know bits of Dain's story, so I won't need to talk about that (Actual excuse is I'm too lazy to research on him)
Then there's Albedo and his Master, which if I remember correctly, the master's name was "Gold" in German or something similar. What was the goal of the two going to mond, that is unsure. But what we do know is Albedo was the destruction of a nation. 

Khaenri'ah without an archon, wanted an archon, and used it's advanced technology, alchemy and knowledge on the closest Archon, Venti, to create an imitation archon, Albedo and Durin, who would share the image of Venti and Dvalin? 
Khaenri'ah most likely created imitation visions/fake visions which would explain the abnormality with Kaeya's own vision. 
The creation of an imitation archon, Albedo, probably angered Celestia, which was what prompted them to force the actual archons to destroy/curse the nation as punishment for that. Albedo's creation brought destruction to a nation which would most likely fit what Dain mentioned about him in his trailer, and Albedo is probably well informed on all of this, since his chance of life destroyed countless others, he's worried something like so will happen again, making him hope the Traveler will stop him if he ever brought a terrible fate to another nation

So the likeliness of Albedo snapping would probably be high, especially when he's in an enemy nation Mondstadt. I have my doubts that his vision is real too, and he is an Homunculus, so wielding two or more visions would most likely not affect him whatsoever.

text:
I have seen several theories of what the trailer showed us, in the comments, since it is only a conflict due to a misunderstanding between Eula and Albedo, the avalanche caused by bennett's bad luck; until the death of our mysterious alchemist; I do not see the latter very likely since it is an event update, and I do not think that the awakening of albedo came from here,  
My 1erfirst theory: taking information from the title of the update, this representation may only be a shadow of snow ( the one who understood understood), since in thorn dragon apparently strange things are happening; Albedo is still alive and reciting poetry around, looking for the thief of his notes, after the avalanche, because I doubt very much that it would pose any risk to a vision bearer.
2dasecond theory: everything is the work of some treasure thief, or the order of the Abyss, who finally want to mess with albedo, after all it is also the creation of the ancient alchemist of kaenriah, which is why he wants to know its true purpose (me I mean albedo), and the emissary from the abyss has corrupted it. since the avalanche was only as a painkiller for the faster process, which I did not achieve with Boreas.But that does not mean that the time bomb has exploded: if one day ... I lose control of myself ... I destroy mondstad ... I destroy everything ... can I count on you to stop me? - Yes, just these words, because the only thing we would do is purify albedo, since the traveler has that power to purify the corrupted energy. but I don't think it will die.

Third and repetitive theory: Eula took her notes, (although I doubt it very much since I do not think that in doing so she made such a mess if we take into account her elegant personality, so most likely she blames her because she sees that she suspected of him without any reason), and what we have seen is really bad albedo because they exhausted his patience, after all he has had a streak of bad luck, an avalanche falls, his notes are stolen for the first time and they leave him in ruins his improvised workshop in thorn dragon, and he can not find the thief, and over there we are and his priority is to protect the people he loves.
Pdta 1: the one I read to the end, well I say thank you for listening to me.
Psdt 2: the one who read this large text in order to throw hate, or say "thank you but nobody asked" well, we all have the right to have an opinion, if you don't like it, what can I do?
Psdt3: If you think that I deny the death of albedo outright, because I am main albedo or simp of this character, then I tell you that you are wrong, I am simp Ei, Ayaka, Kequin and Cannon.

It has to do with Childe's real name and his brothers name being the same as the brothers Ajax and Teucer in Greek mythology from Homer's Iliad and in the Epic Cycle, a series of epic poems about the Trojan War. At the end, Ajax dies. More specifically he kills himself.

text: ¬†@Ty Langs¬† Childe has significantly more than other characters, i'd say. By this i dont mean actual practical probability of death, I mean how it'd fit into the lore and have a significant impact (I doubt mihoyo would kill of someone like, say, diona, since she has little connection to the plot, and her death wouldnt change much)
author: Annabeth Moo

text: ¬†@Annabeth Moo¬† But by that logic, he would still have as much of a death flag as any other character who is lore relevant. Hell if anything I'd say there are other characters whose death would be more impactful like say one of the Archons killed by a God in Celestia. Raiden even alludes that Zhongli's story "is not anywhere near finished yet" and he has the quote "every journey has its final day" which imo puts him over in death flag territory compared to Childe.
author: Ty Langs

text: ¬†@Ty Langs¬† I think one of the reasons people are more concerned over Childe's death flags is that, for one, he is far more impulsive, which could result in his death being more painful (hes also young and hasnt really lived out his whole life yet.) I agree that zhongli also has many death flags, but the ajax-teucer mythology thing gives childe many death points as well. Mihoyo is known to have a lot of information about culture and history and such in their game, and i highly doubt that was just a coincidence.
author: Annabeth Moo

text: ¬†@mymangoo¬† i need sup dps or support characters more, i like his aoe, other than he's handsome lol
author: Eunike Enja Padma Metta

text:
¬†@Annabeth Moo¬† Yeah the Ajax name reference is pretty much the main death flag people point to, but even then I don't see that as any kind of confirmation that he will die. There are already many characters in the game who pull their names from or reference other people or characters, most notably the Archons, yet they don't seem to follow the story of the character they reference directly. Mihoyo is smart enough to understand that if they have a character share the same name with another, people will expect them to have similar stories, doing so would make the story predictable which is exactly why I don't see his story ending verbatim like that of Ajax. There will definitely be similarities and there already are a few but I don't think just him having the name 'Ajax' means he is dying anytime soon. 
Not only that but people seem to be overlooking the fact that he has 2 other names, one of which is a reference to the commedia dell'arte. We know that Scaramouch and Signora follow their counterpart's stories/personalities fairly closely so I don't see why the same wouldn't apply to Tartaglia.
I'm not saying he isn't going to die because no one can really predict what Mihoyo will do, I am just saying that people jump to that conclusion a little too easily and I don't see why his death would be sooner rather than a few years into the story.

text: ¬†@Ty Langs¬† Actually, tartaglia from the play  had a stutter and was farsighted, so he seems fairly timid. it doesn't line up with genshin's tartaglia at all. The fatui harbringer names are almost definitely from commedia, but I think choosing tartaglia to be an odd one out in way was a purposeful choice.
author: Annabeth Moo

text:
¬†@Annabeth Moo¬† No you are exactly right, the character of Tartaglia doesn't exactly fit Childe's personality. Like what I said with the Archons many characters have names that reference others while not actually aligning with that character's story or personality. This is clearly a purposeful decision made to allude to another facet of the character's identity or to lead on to a future change in the character. We can't say which it will be for any given character yet, so at most, we can just speculate. That's why when we go to the name Ajax, the same idea applies, we can't confirm just because they share the same name that they will have the same fate since there are already numerous counter-examples of this. If anything the name might actually be purposely trying to deceive players by making them think he will share the same fate, the truth is that we don't know yet.
The reason I brought up the other Harbingers is because they are cases where a character actually is similar to the character they share their name from, we can't say for certain what this would mean for Childe until we see more Harbingers and how closely they follow their Commedia counter-parts.
author: Ty Langs

text: ¬†@Ty Langs¬† Hm, true, I agree that speculation is all we can truly have and saying that childe is, for certain, going to die, is a little bit of a jump. For me personally, the death flag is both his mannerisms (bLODO MM FIGHTING AHHH)  and ideals (anything is fine as long as i can stab things lol) as well as the mythology thing is what makes him very likely to die, like if he was more composed like a character like Zhongli, there'd probably not be as many people insisting on his impeding doom

text: ¬†@Co¬† yeah in terms of similarities Japanese dub ist the one who is more like original voice over than English. Just taking the Xiao example, in the English version he is harsh and edgy, but in Chinese he is calm and introverted. He isn't edgy but very nice in a strict way. While Japanese and Korean dub did a good job in portraying this, but eng dub made him more aggressive instead. This is no hate against eng dub cuz I like all voice over but it's more often that eng is not as similar as the other dubs than Japanese dub
author: Huijie Wu

text: ¬†@Huijie Wu¬† Yeah, Xiao in the eng dub sounds like a jerk when talking to Ganyu but in the Japanese he does sound calm but also like he doesn't care. text:
¬†@Russell Acosta Mart√≠nez¬† wow, thank you for letting me know, I mean after all I did ask.

text: ¬†@Co¬† yeah I see it the same way. But at the end of the day the differences in the different dubs are simply because every dub has a different voice director and Voice actor and they are all different people. It's logically concludes that they see the situation and characters in different ways and also have different feels while portraying them, so there always differences. Maybe some people feel like that Eula reacting calm in that moment is her being elegant and fits her more, but other people might think her reacting more shocked and surprised like eng dub fits her more because of that shocking moment of albedo attacking her. Every VA is doing great.

text:
Are there really that many likes? Well here's some Itto criticism.
1) His character design should be WAY buffer. Check out Sett's trailer, from league of legends. Now that's a BOSS.
2) His playstyle seems like Baal. Come out press E, Q, hit a few times swap out. 0 dmg auto attacks. Pure def build on artifacts.. Not really a "Boss" character that gets things done himself.
3) Definitely does NOT feel F2P friendly. Everyone can benefit from Att%,CR,CD artifacts but only def scaling characters can benefit from def artifacts. Why waste resin to farm def artifacts when you can focus on artifacts that are beneficial to all characters (Emblem & Shimenawa).
4) Corrosion deals %HP I think? So releasing defense character now seems stupid and out of context of the new boss. Sett would still die from the new world boss without a healer. And to have a 4 man geo team, you must put in Noelle for the heals, which means Noelle will compete with Itto for time on the field. Sounds dumb tbh...

So to sum it up : We might get an event continuing the 1.2 event , And we might need to defeat albedo
This is just my theory I don't know if I'm wrong.

text:
He already had abilities (specifically Alchemy) before he got his vision. And with his Geo vision he just decided to keep it because he wants to study visions. That means he's already capable of controlling many elements and creating life because of Khemia. He's not human and can even use pyro if he wanted. The guy turned a butterfly into a bird and created life with his fingertips.

The requirement of getting a Geo vision is if you're already a competent person and don't even need a vision in the first place. That's why Noelle, Albedo, and Ningguang didn't value their vision when they first got it because they figured that it's not that important for them, until they later accepted it.

Albedo is capable with Alchemy and can create things without the help of a vision. Him being connected to Durin is probably why he's able to use cryo powers. Just my speculation.

I think the avalanche got in the way of whatever keeps him "sane" since there's the remnant of the dragon in Dragonspine. I think he'll just lose control and we will understand who or what he really is
author: Art by Shadow

text: ¬†@Jil 1807¬† Signora is basically a pyro elemental being using a delusion to use cryo. Since Albedo seems not to be human, I suppose he could be somewhat along her line. An elementary being turned human-like by During through Khemia and now he's losing control because of the avalanche. Maybe losing consciousness means he goes berserk and the avalanche hit
author: Art by Shadow

text: ¬†@Guilherme Alves Lopes¬† so that would mean that not only he's not human but he's actually some kind of monster creature turned human by Durin through Khemia much like a rock was turned into Azhdaha by Morax. I mean, only actual geo monsters can use other elements. Regular geo users can only create an elemental shield through crystallize.
author: Art by Shadow

text:
¬†@Yuuri¬† ok, so, he learned Khemia (which in this game is very different from alchemy) and then he received a geo vision. 
Now, from what I've understood about Khaenri'ah and Khemia, it can create life, not elements, so I really don't see a connection between Khemia and cryo powers.
Albedo gave a demonstration about Khemia by bringing to life a dead tree branch and in Khaenri'ah people used it to create what they needed to survive since the land wasn't bountiful.
Now, what I believe is that Albedo was something either like Azhdaha or Signora.
Azhdaha was a rock brought to life by Morax through his Geo power.
Signora is straight up a pyro elemental being who was granted a cryo delusion by the Tsaritsa.
Since Khemia can create life, maybe Albedo is something in between Azhdaha and Signora. Still an elemental being that was granted a human for by Durin through Khemia and them a Geo vision by whoever grants visions.
Maybe the avalanche simply made him lose consciousness and now his true self is going berserk? I honestly can't wait to know what is up with him. 10 days and we'll know
author: Art by Shadow

text: ¬†@Daniel Angelo¬† I went and checked the video frame by frame. They really did a great job at hiding his vision after the avalanche but there is still 1 single frame where we see the gold glow of his vision. You may be right, but there must be something more to it. The avalanche is for sure the cause of his "transformation", but I think his cryo attacks are more related to what he really is behind his human form. There is still Khemia in his story and it can create life. I really think he's an elemental being turned human through Khemia and constantly repressing his true self until the avalanche got him
author: Art by Shadow

text:
¬†@Krillinz¬† no, it's not two visions because he wouldn't have the requirement nor any kind of reason to receive another vision. Also, much like the Raiden Shogun, I don't think anyone is getting new cryo visions. I have a feeling that even though the archon don't decide who should receive one, they still have some kind of meaning in the bestowal of visions, like it's their will of giving visions in general together with the possession of the gnosis that people are able to receive one and I don't think the Tsaritsa is looking forward to giving people visions.
I think you're mistaking alchemy with Khemia btw. He is an expert in Khemia, the old alchemy from Khaenri'ah that can create life. I think it has something to do with this, but there must be something more behind his cryo powers...
author: Art by Shadow

text:
¬†@Art by Shadow¬† its interesting when I thought of it, but Khemia is the process of taking the chalk from the earth and making into gold, or life. Perhaps the geo vision is his chalk form and cryo is his gold form. 

Most of the enemies that are said to be from gold are actually equipped with mechanised components made by humans, the wolves for example are said to be of gold but their claws are actually only constructs of metal that hasn't transformed during Khemia. Maybe the unaffected component is his vision.
author: Daniel Angelo

text:
¬†@Daniel Angelo¬† taking into consideration what you said, it's probably the opposite actually. Khemia transforms chalk into gold. We know that Durin did something with Khemia on him. Maybe his cryo for is the chalk that was transformed by Rhinedottir (who I stupidly kept calling Durin without realizing that was the dragon...) into gold, i.e. the Albedo form.
You know what? I'll throw it there even if it may make no sense. Maybe Albedo's real form is actually some kind of elemental for from Dragonspine back when it was an hinabitable nation that was found by Rhinedottir and was given a new life with Khemia and now, with the avalanche, he got reverted back or his past life re-emerged and lost control over the Albedo form. Everything is possible in Genshin Impact.
I mean, Azhdaha is probably a star that fell in the Chasm from the sky and was transformed into a living being by Morax. We know Rhinedottir was/is obsessed with Khemia. Maybe she just experimented on an elemental being like Azhdaha but from Dragonspine and managed to give it life.

author: Jil 1807

text:
Oh, I actually know that Khemia is meant to be a type of alchemy, however it doesn't follow equivalent exchange, so its similar to full metal alchemist where if you don't have the equal resources for the outcome it becomes corrupted, similar to what happened to Durin blood and corpse and possibly khaen'riah, which affected their bodies and transformed them into hilichurls.

Also they explain that Khemia is element-less because it wasn't created by the seven archons and utilised by Khaen'riah due to them not needing the magic that the archons gift, which means that Albedo wouldn't get cryo from this accident.

Signora however was actually so superheated that in order for her to survive, Il Dottore chemically implanted her cryo delusion, which was gifted to her by the cryo archon, inside her to prevent her from combusting, similarly to the Versailles witch which was what she was meant to represent in Genshin.

text:
Fun Fact: The ruins in Dragonspine are remains of a civilization called Sal Vindagnyr, and this was built/founded by citizens of Old Mondstadt who fled the said city due to the late God of Tower Decarabian's harsh way of ruling over them. By this information, we can assume that Sal Vindagnyr was a godless nation like Khaenri'ah which existed during the Archon War. 

The civilization was ruled by a lineage of priests who can read leylines, until Celestia dropped the Skyfrost Nail to destroy Sal Vindagnyr and the Frostbearing Tree where the priests get their leylines. Exact date of Sal Vindagnyr's destruction is yet to be confirmed.

PS Frostbearing Tree got revived by the blood of the dragon Durin who was defeated and died in Dragonspine during the cataclysm 500 years ago.

text:
¬†@Moin Shaikh¬† yes, thank you for mentioning that too! Imunlaukr, the adventurer whom befriended the last princess of Sal Vindagnyr. Before continuing his journey, Imunlaukr promised the princess he'd return to the city. Unfortunately, when he came back, Sal Vindagnyr and the princess is no more.

Devastated by this loss, Imunlaukr would later participate in a war "at the far north" which would most likely be the revolution against Decarabian led by Barbatos, the Nameless Bard, and an unnamed knight.

Imunlaukr ended up as an aristocrat of early days of the current Mondstadt and became the ancestor of Imunlaukr Clan‚Äîa family of aristocrats who worshipped both the God of Wind and the God of Time. 

For some unknown reasons, however, the Imunlaukr Clan's lineage declined, and no confirmed/known descendant is around during the current timeline of the game.

Edit: The snow-tombed claymore was supposed to be a gift from Sal Vindagnyr's princess to Imunlaukr.

author: ailam hassan

text:
‚Äã¬†@seke¬† I can help if you're on europe server, or you can ask someone.
Otherwise aggro all of them and make them teleport next to each other, then try to kill them with aoe attacks. I used Xiangling and Bennett to pop their bubbles at once, if you have Sucrose or someone better like Venti or Kazuha to keep them together its even better, and if your character has the "wet" status just switch to a different one so they dont freeze you, the only problem left is the time, where you just need to master your strategy and get lucky
author: D√ÜMoN

text: ¬†@Annisa Muthia¬† After getting into Dragonspine, you need to unlock some orbs to get to the summit of Dragonspine. One if them is near the frostbearing tree, one of them is near the place the cryo hypostatsis is, and one of them is in the area inside of Dragonspine. The one inside Dragonspine is god awful. There is a half frozen over lake, with some solid ground and gaps between. Made traversing a nightmare. You basically had to build muscle memory to jump across the gaps. there are also ice samachurls, which can summon ice spikes anywhere and those instantly freeze you most of the time. you have to run across, get to the border, kill the samachurls, then kill the hilichurls, and instantly dash across the lake. Then, you have to go to the next place, kill both samachurls before they can summon a pillar, and then get across to the last place. You need to hop across the ice platforms before one of the abyss mages can apply cryo to you making freezing. inevitable. Then, you need to melt their shields, kill them both in the remaining like, 15 or so seconds. Yeah, it's an absolutely horrible hell of an experience.

text:
I mean, there's the theory of Paimon the Star God or whatever, with Paimon's bargains and whatnot, providing us characters and their contellations, suggesting that the characters in our party are not literally with us, but rather they are a stellar projection of their personality and memories. So a character who is playable could possibly die in the story. Not saying that is happening here, or ever, even, but I wouldn't rule it out as a possibility is all.

Also Albedo is like, a humonculous, a creation of alchemy, and I am pretty sure it is the same fundamental technology that created Scaramouche and the Raiden Shogun "puppets". They are creations, but of an organic nature, rather than the obviously mechanical origins of ruin guards etc. And if a puppet can be made, it can be re-made.

The thing that interests me now, is like, wtf, albedo wielding two elements?! The only other examples I can think of (in terms of humanoid characters, so excluding Azdaha) are Childe with his delusion, Signora with her maybe-but-maybe-not-delusion-or-something, now dead, (but as with above could be reborn?... I've heard theories of her also being a "puppet", probably in the Tsaritsa's image), and of course Kazuha, when his dead friend's vision reawakened. I don't know what this means, I can't see if Albedo has a second vision here, and if he does, no doubt it would be hidden until we actually see it in game, whose would it be, another dead friend, a complete stranger, dead or otherwise, granted to him in the same manner as normal?... I thought this at when Kazuha did the thing, but does this mean we will get playable dual element characters in the future?

So many possibilities, so excited üòÅ

text: ¬†@Alpha 2081¬† Venti don't preside over Mondstadt, yes, but he is still the center of their worship. Their kind of faith is inspired from the religious faith we have in the real world: they worship regardless if they see their god or not. The Church is literally at the highest point of the city and Barbatos' statue is the grandest of statues we see so far for a reason. There's a psychology behind positioning of religious things, their size, and it's relation to faith. So it's not right to say his people doesn't worship him a lot. Even Stanley, despite being an adventure and losing the real Stanley and going through a lot, always believes in Barbatos. If there are anyone who doesn't, that's probably some of the Lawrence Clan. But they know he exists, they just don't want to accept it. And regarding the fight with Durin, having 2 against 1 doesn't mean that 1 cannot defeat or is weaker than the enemy. Take Morax for example, even he had the help of the adepti during the Archon War, but does that mean he is weaker than his enemy? No. And take Ei for instance, she can easily obliterate what she wants yet she fights with an army, does that make her weak? Definitely not. So Barbatos using the help of Dvalin during the fight against Durin doesn't mean Barbatos is weaker than Durin or he can't take it down himself. After all, Durin showed in Mondstadt City, Barbatos cannot simply focus on fighting Durin when his people are becoming casualties. In a fight, you can't always be offensive, you need to take other factors into consideration. You can't just go all out and hope for the best while people are losing their lives. They had to divert Durin from the city to Dragonspine and also make sure people are safe. You are assuming that getting is help means being weak. The archons are not omnipotent, but they are THE Archons for a reason. And also, read more about what really happened in that event. Even if Albedo's master created Durin, Durin was manipulated by the power of the Abyss. So aside from the power he might have, he was also controlled by the power of the Abyss. And that very power is said to be the only thing that can turn Morax's pillar into ash of sort. Hopefully this helps you realize many other things you seem to had overlooked.
